k), tell you that after much deep contemplation they have figured out that religion is &quot;pointless&quot; and &quot;just a way to control people&quot;?<br>
<br>
Rambling about how &quot;Religion is just a way for the people in power to control the masses dude&quot; is the mantra for every social reject who fancies himself a deep-thinking intellectual. Dismissing people who are religious as being idiots and needing a crutch is a pitiful, if you're so @#%$ smart and can see through the illusion of religion so clearly what are you doing wasting your time on Nameless Taven? You should be putting that amazing intellect to work solving the terrorism crisis, promoting world peace and curing cancer. Hasn't it occurred to you that if in the whole of recorded history, with all of the millions of people who have tread the earth, even the smartest among them has been not able to prove the answer on way or another is because the answer isn't something as vapid as &quot;religion is just a way to control people&quot;?<br>
<br>
You don't find the answers to life's greatest questions by daydreaming about them in 4th period studyhall. Go out and do some reading,(not asinine EQ message boards, actual BOOKS by influential authors would be best), talk to some educated people who are also passionate about their faith and start to form your views from there and *then* maybe you'll be able to offer a somewhat enlightened opinion on the validity of religion and faith rather than making yourself look like a fool by spouting some simplistic babble inspired by something a goth chick told you while you were drinking maddog behind a dumpster at halftime of some high school sporting event.<br>
<br>
I'd be embarrassed if I made a statement like &quot;religion is pointless&quot; and then had absolutely nothing of substance to back it up with and you should be too. Do us all a favor and go out and learn something before you decide to try and take down one of the pillars of human civilization next time ok?<br>
